pfehlungen zur selbständigen Weiterarbeit verknüpft.  aTraveling in the Roman Empire is still a fascinating subject today: infrastructure and logistics met the highest standards of premodern mobility, which is why trips for recreation and education were very popular with the Romans. This volume uses selected sources to present reasons for traveling, itineraries, and travel destinations. It connects an overview of basic knowledge with exercises and reading recommendations for independent study.  aIssued also in print.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn German.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 06. Mrz 2024) 0aTravel, Ancient. 4aGeschichte des Reisens. 4aLehrbuch. 4aQuellen. 4aRömische Antike. 4aStudienbuch. 7aHISTORY / Ancient / General.2bisacsh  aRoman antiquity.  ahistory of travel.  asources.  atextbook.08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertDG Plus DeG Package 2023 Part 1z978311117578208iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE COMPLETE 2023z9783111318912oZDB-23-DGG08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE History 2023z9783111318189oZDB-23-DEG0 cEPUBz97831107636520 cprintz978311076323240uhttps://doi.org/10.1515/978311076358440uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9783110763584423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9783110763584/original  a978-3-11-117578-2  DG Plus DeG Package 2023 Part 1b2023  aEBA_CL_HICS  aEBA_DGALL  aEBA_EBKALL  aEBA_SSHALL  aGBV-deGruyter-alles  aZDB-23-DEGb2023  aZDB-23-DGGb2023